advantage of Linkedlist :

1.dynamic Data structure (allocates needd memory whike running)
2.insertion and deletion of node is easy . 0(1)
3.No/low memory wasted

disadvantang : 

1. greater memory usage (additional pointer)
2. no random access of elements (no index[i])
3.Acessing/ searching element is more time consuming. O(n)

what we using Linkedlist for  

1. implement Stack/ queues
2.GPS navigation 
3.Music Playlist; 


                   IV. Dynamic Array 

    also call in java = araraylist
    C++ = vector
    javascript = Array
    python = list

A dynamic array is an array that can automatically change its size while the program is running.

so here an example of static array what is static array ?

A static array is the simplest type of array in programming. 
It has a fixed size, which means the number of elements it can hold is
 decided when you create it and cannot change later.

 example static array : 

 given capacity : 5 , size : depend on value in array 
ok at first u have 5 empty slot and 4 data_Value

0     1    2     3     4
_A__.__B_.__C__.__D___._____ ; so the size are 3

0     1    2     3     4
_A__.__B_.__C__.__D___.__E___ ; 

so the max size are 5 and it capacity that it can hold only 5;

remember we given capacity 5 ; see we can create it but
we cant increas the capacity after so that why they create 
Dynamic array will increasing size automatically while the program 
running 


ArrayList<Integer> list = new ArrayList<>(2); // initial capacity = 2

list.add(1);
list.add(2);
list.add(3); // <-- here ArrayList increases capacity automatically

#NOTE IMPORTTAND !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
Two files: DynamicArray.java and Main.java

DynamicArray.java → contains the class DynamicArray.
 This class has all the instructions for
 how a dynamic array works (like adding, printing, resizing).

Main.java → uses DynamicArray to do things in your program (like adding elements and printing them).


